text: I'm not a huge fan of Blightsteel myself. It's been my experience that it either sits in  your hand unpalyable, gets stolen via Bribery before it gets played, or worse gets stole AFTER you dump 12 mana into it, or it just gets Path'ed immediately and you Time Walked yourself. That might entirely be a meta thing, but it almost always does more damage to the person running it. YMMV entirely there.

I'd personally run Chaos Warp over Oblivion Strike. I'd probalby run Sever the Bloodline over Oblivion Strike, but I'd definitely run Chaos Warp first, unless I'm missing some synergy with devoid, which is entirely possible.

Again, a meta call, but I always feel like there's too many Skullclamps or Ashnod's Altars floating around to use Forbidden Orchard without some real synergy (Glissa/Mindslaver or something). Myself, i'd just run City of Brass or Exotic Orchard.

IMO decks running more than a few creatures that you absolutely do NOT want hitting you in the face should run Homeward Path. I'm probably not putting it in a token deck or elfball or anything, but a deck with scary dragons and demons and eldrazi and stuff like Blightsteel and Deus of Calamity is absolutely getting a Path.

6 of 1, half a dozen of the other, but I can't think of the last time I've needed to blow up a land on turns 1-4, probalby in part becuase I use land removal for problem lands an not color denial. Because of that I'd rather pay 1 with a Tec Edge and NOT let them replace the land than do it for no mana with a Ghost Quarter but be down 1 to the rest of the table.

Burgeoning is a great card, but I'm not sure there's enough draw here to consistently get enough out of it? The commander draws, Phyrexian Arena, Erebos can, and Sylvan Library can, but I'm not qsure that's quite enough. It feels like it's going to be a card you play, play a second land on one person's turn, then maybe use once more a few turns later, and that's it. At that point I'd probably rather just Skyshround Claim to get the guarenteed ramp that isn't reliant on only working if you have multiple lands in hand multiple times.
Great insights as always. Thanks man.
